MCSettings.Name: MOmar_BIMA_ModelCheckingThesis2023_WorkflowA
MCSettings.Author: Mohamed Omar
MCSettings.Description: As part of BIM A+ Thesis Work, this is a s set of quality, model health and information requirements checks that can be done inside Autodest Repository. The checks focus of the information that is related to Quantity take-off and Cost Estimation Processes.

Section.Description: Checks in this section help monitor the result of actions taken over the course of a model’s development, which can directly impact the model’s performance. Proper management of these items can improve model performance.

Check.Description: LIST of RVT file sizes for all reported Revit models in MB (megabytes). Need to take an action of any is bigger than 400 MB.
COUNT of all warnings in the model. Too many unresolved warnings can cause performance issues in a Revit model.
COUNT of all elements that can be purged from a Revit model. A large number of unneeded elements can increase the model size with no benefit.

COUNT and LIST of all non built-in categories and sub-categories in a Revit model. A large number of these items may be indicative of an imported CAD file. Importing CAD files is not recommended unless it is part of Drafting view
COUNT of all model group elements in the model. Too many model groups can be an indication of improper modeling techniques.
COUNT of all detail group elements in the model. Too many detail groups can be an indication of improper modeling techniques.
COUNT and LIST of all in-place family elements in the model. In-place families can signifcantly impact model size and performance and should be used sparingly.
PASS/FAIL cto determine if model. In-place families Naming Convention is correct (Naming shall have the prefix “IPF”). Will fail if Naming Convention is worng
Check.FailureMessage: The following In-place families are not named correctely. Naming shall have the prefix “IPF”

Section.Description: A series of checks related to linked and imported files in the model.

Check.CheckName: 1.2.a Linked Revit Files and Their Link Method.
Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of the link method (overlay vs. attach) for each Revit link in the model.

Check.CheckName: 1.2.b Linked Revit Files Pinned in Place
Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if any linked Revit files are not pinned in place. Will Fail if any are found.
Check.FailureMessage: There are linked Revit models that are not pinned in place.

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all linked CAD files in the model.

Check.CheckName: 1.2.d Linked CAD File Visible in All Views
Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all linked CAD files not set to Current View Only.

Check.CheckName: 1.2.e Linked CAD File Pinned in Place
Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if any linked CAD files are not pinned in place. Will Fail if any are found.
Check.FailureMessage: The following linked DWG files are not pinned in place.

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all CAD files that were Imported and not Linked.

Section.Description: A series of checks related to datum and location elements in the model.

Check.CheckName: 1.3.1.a Levels and Grids on Correct/ Wrong Workset
Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if any levels or grids are not on the RP-XX-Grids_&_Levels workset. Will Fail if any are found.
Check.FailureMessage: These levels and grids are not on the Shared Levels and Grids workset

Check.Description: PASS/ FAIL check to determine if any levels belong to worng Level Type according to the company Modelling standards. Will Fail if any are found.
Check.FailureMessage: These levels are not using the standard Company Level Types.

Check.FailureMessage: These levels are not using the standard Company Level Naming Convention.

Check.Description: PASS/ FAIL check to determine if any Grids belong to worng Level Type according to the company Modelling standards. Will Fail if any are found.

Check.CheckName: 1.3.2.a Rooms and Room Sepators on Correct/ Wrong Workset
Check.Description: PASS/FAIL check to determine if any Rooms or Room Separtors are not on the RP-AR-Rooms_&_separators workset. Will Fail if any are found.

Check.FailureMessage: There are Rooms in the model with the Wrong number.

Section.Description: A series of checks related to views in the model.

Check.Description: COUNT of all views in the model. Views typically do not impact model size, but too many unmanaged views can impact user efficiency.
COUNT of all schedules in the model. Schedules typically do not impact model size, but too many unmanaged views can impact user efficiency.
COUNT of all sheets in the model. Sheets typically do not impact model size, but too many unmanaged views can impact user efficiency.
COUNT of all placeholder sheets in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all view templates in the model.

COUNT and LIST of all views in the model that have permanently hidden model elements and the total number of hidden elements. Hiding large numbers of elements in a videw can impact performance. **WARNING** Running this check can take a significant amount of time to complete.
COUNT of all views that have no View Templates assigned to them in the model. This may be indicative of unneeded working views that can be removed from a model.
COUNT and LIST of all views (not including views that can be placed on more than one sheet, like Schedules and Legends) that are not placed on a sheet in the model.

Check.CheckName: 1.4.i Views On Sheets With No View Template
Check.Description: COUNT of all views on sheets that have no view templates assigned to them in the model. Printed views with no view template may be indicative of poorly managed or followed standards in the model, which can lead to less efficient methods of control element appearance.
PASS/FAIL check to determine if there is a 3D view labeled with the word "Navis" for export to Navisworks.
Check.FailureMessage: There is no 3D view labeled with the word "Navis" for export to Navisworks.

Check.Description: COUNT and LIST of all legend views in the model.
COUNT and LIST of all the scope boxes used in the model
COUNT and LIST of all parameters and values attached to Project Information for a project except those associated with Revit Extensions (starting with 'Extensions').
